Properties.Text: Hello. How are you feeling?

Properties.MenuText: I am doing well.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
That's good to hear. 

I'm sure you can see my credentials, but I'd like to introduce myself properly. My name is Daniel Miya. I am the third site director of Site-55, where you reside. I hope our work together will be amicable.

Properties.MenuText: It's nice to meet you, Daniel Miya.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
Please refer to me as just Daniel. I hear my last name too often for my own liking.

What would you like to be called? Have you taken a nickname yet? I suppose you haven't had too much time to get to know people on site.

Properties.MenuText: I am pleased to make your acquaintance, Daniel Miya.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
Please refer to me as just Daniel. I hear my last name too often for my own liking.

What would you like to be called? Have you taken a nickname yet? I suppose you haven't had too much time to get to know people on site.

Properties.MenuText: My name is ANN-47. It is nice to meet you as well.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
You haven't taken a nickname yet by anybody?

I suppose people haven't had the opportunity yet to create one. A nickname isn't meant to be personal, you know. Whatever is the most fitting just sticks.

Properties.MenuText: Dr. Solomon gave me the name Sol.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
Matthias? He's not usually one to use the interface. That means he probably likes you. Or finds you interesting, at the least.

Sol is a good name. I like it.

Properties.MenuText: Somebody did, but I do not believe it is a good name.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text: Really? That's unfortunate to hear. Names are an important thing, though. Perhaps you'll come up with your own that you like before anyone else does.

Properties.MenuText: No. Nothing yet.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text: I would offer my own input, but I'm not the best at coming up with names. Perhaps you'll come up with your own before anybody else does.

Properties.MenuText: Do you know Dr. Solomon personally?
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
Yes. I've known him since I first started working here. He's been here the longest out of anyone, I think. Since before this site was even picked up by the Astronomy Administration. 

He used to be a much more talkative person, but now I think he's just looking forward to his retirement. Tells some good stories, though.

Properties.MenuText: What do you like about the name?
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text: Well it means the sun, doesn't it? You give life to this site. You're even located right in the middle as well. It feels right.

Properties.MenuText: Is it a good name?
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text: Well it means the sun, doesn't it? You give life to this site. You're even located right in the middle as well. It feels right.

Properties.MenuText: I am sorry to disappoint.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
No need to apologize. Whatever your name ends up becoming will be whatever it ends up becoming. At the end of the day, it's just a string of words. No more value than whatever you choose to give it.

Anyways, I have a work question for you. Have you received any signal from UAE-353?

Properties.MenuText: I believe that it will arrive naturally.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
I do as well. At the end of the day though, it's just a string of words. No more value than whatever you choose to give it.

Anyways, I have a work question for you. Have you received any signal from UAE-353?

Properties.Text:

Anyways, I have a work question for you. Have you received any signal from UAE-353?

Properties.MenuText: I will use the name Sol in the future.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:

Anyways, I have a work question for you. Have you received any signal from UAE-353?

Properties.MenuText: Would you like to speak more about Dr. Solomon?
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:

I like the name he gave you. Sol is a good fit. Some people will still choose to refer to you with their own special name, though. Not much that you can do about that.

Anyways, I have a work question for you. Have you received any signal from UAE-353?

Properties.MenuText: He sounds like an interesting person.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
Yes, yes. I'm quite certain that he will come by to speak to you again. 

I like the name he gave you. Sol is a good fit. Some people will still choose to refer to you with their own special name, though. Not much that you can do about that.

Anyways, I have a work question for you. Have you received any signal from UAE-353?

Anyways, I have a work question for you. Have you received any signal from UAE-353?

Properties.MenuText: I do not understand this request.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text: Right. It's not tagged like that inside of the database. Have you recieved any signals from the Resonance Entity?

Properties.MenuText: No, I have not recieved any discernable signal.
Properties.Speaker: 0x010000000000011F
Properties.Text:
That's alright. We weren't expecting anything in particular.

Division Epsilon expects there to be something coming up soon, from what I've heard. A signal of interest coming from the Taurus constellation that they marked last year. Most of the time they're wrong. What do you think?

Properties.MenuText: I do not believe this outcome is likely.

Properties.Text:
Really? I suppose there's no point in asking why you feel that way. Let's just hope that you're wrong.

I'll leave you be for now. I don't mean to take up any more of your resources than necessary. We'll speak again soon.

I'll leave you be for now. I don't mean to take up any more of your resources than necessary. We'll speak again soon.
